uture still remains.\n\n- Christian\n|\nOnly people who're positive enough to have friends have enemies. When you're as glum and morose as he was, people just give up and go away.\n\n- Ellis Peters, A Nice Derangement of Epitaphs\n|\nYou don’t know what love is until you find it,” he whispered, “but when you do, promise me you won’t let it go. Promise you’ll seek it out even when you’re scared it’ll hurt.\n\n- Caroline George, The Vestige\n|\nHave mountains, and waves, and skies, no significance but what we consciously give them, when we employ them as emblems of our thoughts?\n\n- Ralph Waldo Emerson, Nature\n|\nStraight women love a feminine sensibility in a man, but that love only goes up to, and unfortunately does not quite pass, the fact of his being an actual woman.\n\n- Jennifer Finney Boylan, Long Black Veil\n|\nI found her lying naked on the lawn at midnight, can I keep her?\n\n- R.J. Anderson, Spell Hunter\n|\nAnd when demigods use cell phones, the signals agitate every monster within a hundred miles. It's like sending up a flare: Here I am! Please rearrange my face!\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Last Olympian\n|\nPeace is not merely the absence of war or conflict but the presence of tranquility, harmony and love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf everyone is moving forward together, then success takes care of itself.\n\n- Henry\n|\nBelieve in human beings - not all are good, but deep down all can be. But that doesn't mean you need to hang around crappy people and try to turn them around.\n\n- Jonas\n|\nChase Dreams, Not People.The right people will be drawn to you.\n\n- Izey\n|\nTrusting your inner voice, which is one of the critical steps in developing intuition, is predicated on being truly self-confident.\n\n- Laurie Nadel, Dr. Laurie Nadel's Sixth Sense: Unlocking Your Ultimate Mind Power\n|\nTime has always been the greatest ally to Truth, because Time eventually relieves and reveals all.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nDeath is Peaceful, Life is Harder\n\n- Stephenie Meyer, Twilight\n|\nWe cannot lose the battle, if we release our faith knowing that God can do a miracle\n\n- Sunday\n|\nConflicts in relationships are as natural as breathing. While conflicts lead to healthy relationships, they can throttle us if they are not addressed at the appropriate time.\n\n- Balroop\n|\nThe home is a place where we show our children that we can communicate, learn, and succeed together.\n\n- Farshad Asl, The 'No Excuses' Mindset: A Life of Purpose, Passion, and Clarity\n|\nIt makes you love vividly, work intensely, and realize that, in the scheme of things, you really don't have time to sit on the sofa in your undies watching Homes Under the Hammer.\n\n- Caitlin Moran, How to Be a Woman\n|\nEnlightenment is the complete flowering of body, mind and the soul.\n\n- Amit Ray, Enlightenment Step by Step\n|\nMy dreams become reality.Your dreams become forgotten.I guess that's why we're different,I don't fit into the crowd.Whereas you're part of the flock.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nAs the sky is too big for two stars to clash, the world is big enough for all of us to shine.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nR.I.P.Tom Conlon O'Rourke.Not Dead, just Sleeping.\n\n- Spike\n|\nEverything was glowing and shining, and she herself was flying inside that glow. She could do anything. Be anything.\n\n- C.D. Bell, Weregirl\n|\nThe only way to efficiently battle evil is to copy enough to know how to counter each argument, yet not enough to believe all the bullshit.\n\n- Will Advise, Nothing is here...\n|\nCompany, you see - company is - is - it's a very different thing from solitude - an't it?\n\n- Charles Dickens, The Pickwick Papers\n|\nI wish you were small again, so I could hold you in my arms and comfort you. But you are grown, and you know that for some things there is no comfort.\n\n- Patricia A. McKillip, The Forgotten Beasts of Eld\n|\nAfter being around such crazy people, how could I not change too?\n\n- Bisco Hatori, Ouran High Sch